result.execSummary:
The defendant Ileana D. Henry was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Ileana D. Henry is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Ileana D. Henry was found guilty of Criminal Trespass to Dwelling, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.14.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: ADA Melissa Inlow appears for the State.  Defendant appeared in person and with Attorney Sherman.  State moved to amend Count 1 to criminal trespass to dwelling, 943.14 class A misdemeanor.  Granted.  Victim notification complied with.  Plead to amended Count 1.    Dismiss Counts 2 and 3.  Court recited the charge and possible penalties of the count she is pleading to.  She understood.  Defendant plead no contest.  Court reviewed the plea questionnaire, constitutional rights and elements with the defendant.  Defendant understood.  Defense stipulated that there is a factual basis for the plea.   Court found that the defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently entered her plea and waived her constitutional rights.  Court found that a factual basis exists for the plea.  Found guilty of amended Count 1. Counts 2 and 3 dismissed.   Joint recommendation for 200.00, plus costs.  Defendant did not exercise her right to allocution.  Court ordered $200, plus costs.  Total $515.00, plus DNA surcharge.  Pay @$100/mo starting 2/1/16.   Failure to pay any part of the fine or court costs in full by the due date will result in 1 day jail for each $25 left unpaid.
